        "@language": "en-us",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\t\n\n\n\n\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\tChange your cover photoUpload Change your cover photoUpload\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tApply\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t Cancel\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\tAshley Au\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tThis user account status is Approved\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tAbout\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tAbout\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tPosts\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tPosts\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tComments\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tComments\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\tThis user has not added any information to their profile yet.Member TypeFull MemberE-mail Addressashley@ashleyau.comWebsite URLhttp://www.ashleyau.comPhone Number2042908781Design Discipline(s)SoundPreferred Pronoun(s)She/TheyResidence — Province/TerritoryManitobaLanguages SpokenEnglishResidence — RegionWinnipegInstagramInstagramLinkedInLinkedInSoundCloudSoundCloudBioAshley Au is a Winnipeg-based bassist, composer, sound artist, arranger, and queer creative.\nA multifaceted musician, Ashley specializes in the upright and electric basses—performing, touring and recording internationally for the better part of the last decade. As a composer and sound artist, Ashley’s work can be found behind various theatre, opera and dance productions as well as Winnipeg’s ephemeral pop-up stages.\nAfter completing a degree in Jazz Bass Performance (B. Mus) at Brandon University, under the direction of Michael Cain, Greg Gatien, Eric Platz, and Gilles Fournier, Ashley has become an active member of Winnipeg’s arts and cultural community as a performer, administrator and organizer.\nAs an administrator, Ashley has worked in literary publishing, visual arts, dance, and of course, music. Ashley is the current artistic director of Cluster New Music + Integrated Arts Festival and the stage producer for the Pride Winnipeg Festival. She also co-ordinates a BIPOC poetry writing workshop series through Contemporary Verse 2, Canada’s oldest poetry journal.\nCurrent and past projects include work with Weakerthans frontman, John K. Samson; chamber folk songwriter, Christine Fellows; folk roots songstress, Carly Dow; internationally-acclaimed Americana tastemaker, Scott Nolan; composer/jazz trumpeter Chuck Copanace; the Royal Manitoba Theatre Centre; Winnipeg’s Contemporary Dancers; and Polaris Prize-nominated live hip-hop outfit, Super Duty Tough Work among others.Available for Work?YesAvailable for Assistant/Associate WorkNo\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\n\t\t\t.um-113.um {\n\t\t\tmax-width: 1000px;\n\t\t}\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t.um-113.um .um-profile-body {\n\t\t\tmax-width: 600px;\n\t\t}\n\t\t.um-113.um .um-profile-photo a.um-profile-photo-img {\n\t\twidth: 190px;\n\t\theight: 190px;\n\t}\n\t.um-113.um .um-profile-photo a.um-profile-photo-img {\n\t\ttop: -105px;\n\t}\n\t\t\t.um-113.um .um-profile-meta {\n\t\t\tpadding-left: 250px;\n\t\t}\n\t\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
